Compile photographs of and showcase by appropriate exhibits, Biliran landmarks, historical sites and scenic views;

4.8.

Gather specimens of archaeological findings, and collect major minerals present in Biliran, namely, gypsum, sulfur, and white clay and such other geological materials unique to Biliran in coordination with the concerned cultural agency such as the National Museum of the Philippines and the like;

4.9.

Preserve by appropriate methods samples of flora and fauna to the Province of Biliran;

4.10.

Conduct performances on local music, dances, arts, literary works, epics, stories, historical accounts and legends; and

4.11.

Carry out any other relevant and appropriate activities, such as but not limited to the following:

4.11.1

Maintain and update an inventory with proper evaluation and documentation of all cultural properties within Biliran;

4.11.2

Document the traditional and contemporary arts and crafts of Biliran, including their processes and makers and sustain the sources of their raw materials;

4.11.3

Conduct field assessment/verification of sites in coordination with the NCCA pursuant to Section 28 of Republic Act No. 10066;

